Rating: 0
My favorite recipe to bring to holiday parties. I always get compliments and requests for the recipe. 2 tbsp of oil for saute, 4 tbsp for the marinade. I also reduce the dill to 1 tbsp and add 1 tbsp of fresh cilantro. Perfect balance. If you mince the garlic finely (which is what minced means) it reduces it's powerful flavor and helps it blend better. I haven't found the need to rinse the capers personally. If your pan won't accommodate the entire amount of shrimp in a single layer, then cook it in smaller batches. Better to cook the shrimp on the underdone side as it does continue to "cook" in the marinade. I've made this recipe countless times and have never failed to get compliments.

