Rating: 3
We made this recipe using giant jumbo shrimp fresh from the gulf coast. I have to say that the smell of the marinade put me off a bit, and first tastes did not give encouragement either, but after sitting in the marinade all day the shrimp turned out pretty well. I thought the flavors were strong on the shrimp and have to say that a large, large and fresh shrimp is ideal for enough of the shrimp flavor to remain and come through at all. I did saute the shrimp with the chopped garlic, and that smell alone was to die for! So for me the ify marinade was a gamble. Doubt this will ever get made again, but it was nice and different enough for Christmas Eve.

